OrQ_aFG"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["confusion matrix:\n","\n","A confusion matrix is a table used to evaluate the performance of a classification model. It compares the model's predicted labels with the actual labels, helping you see where the model is making correct and incorrect predictions.\n","\n","Binary Classification Confusion Matrix\n","Actual / Predicted\tPositive\tNegative\n","Positive\tTrue Positive (TP)\tFalse Negative (FN)\n","Negative\tFalse Positive (FP)\tTrue Negative (TN)\n","What each term means\n","True Positive (TP): The model correctly predicts the positive class.\n","Example: A patient has a disease, and the model predicts they have the disease.\n","True Negative (TN): The model correctly predicts the negative class.\n","Example: A healthy patient is correctly predicted as healthy.\n","False Positive (FP): The model incorrectly predicts the positive class.\n","Also called a Type I error.\n","Example: A healthy patient is incorrectly predicted to have the disease.\n","False Negative (FN): The model incorrectly predicts the negative class.\n","Also called a Type II error.\n","Example: A patient with the disease is incorrectly predicted as healthy."],"metadata":{"id":"kUpq9kev_dtH"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Accuracy\n","\n","Recall\n","\n","precision\n","\n","Fscore"],"metadata":{"id":"-QRySRNRB5lm"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"metadata":{"id":"PaBgd1D6G4Tk","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783055433171,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":708,"user":{"displayName":"Ranveer CTU2400182","userId":"00008970564212507249"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","from sklearn import linear_model"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["data = sns.load_dataset('iris')\n","data.head()"],"metadata":{"id":"eqXYTNs4EMDo","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":206},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783055433200,"u